    Combine two qseaSets

    combineQsetsList.Rd

    This function takes a list of qseaSets (or strings to read rds files from) and merges them together

    combineQsetsList(
  qseaSets,
  firstQset = NULL,
  dropDuplicates = TRUE,
  checkParams = TRUE,
  regionsToKeep = NULL
)

    Arguments

    qseaSets

    A list of qseaSet objects or strings to rds files with them in

    firstQset

    An first qseaSet object to combine the rest into (optional)

    dropDuplicates

    Whether to drop samples with the same name. Else renames them by adding "_Dup" to the end of the name.

    checkParams

    Whether to verify that all the parameters are identical in both objects

    regionsToKeep

    A GRanges object (or table coercible to one) to use to subset the samples. Helps keep RAM use down.

    Value

    A qseaSet object, containing all the samples from both qseaSet objects.
